# 1. What is Docker Compose?

Docker Compose is a tool used to run **multiple containers together** using a single YAML file.

Without Compose:

```text
docker run frontend

docker run backend

docker run postgres
```

Every container has to be started manually.

With Compose:

```bash
docker compose up -d
```

Everything starts automatically.

---

# 2. Why Did We Use Docker Compose?

Our application has three different components.

```text
Frontend

↓

Backend

↓

PostgreSQL
```

All three must communicate with each other.

Docker Compose makes this communication automatic.

---

# 3. Life Before Docker Compose

Suppose Docker Compose didn't exist.

You would do something like this:

```text
Start PostgreSQL

↓

Create Network

↓

Start Backend

↓

Connect Backend to Network

↓

Start Frontend

↓

Connect Frontend

↓

Check Logs

↓

Application Ready
```

Many manual steps.

---

# Docker Compose Solution

One YAML file.

One command.

```bash
docker compose up -d
```

Everything starts in the correct order.

