# 16. Interview Questions

### Q1. Why Docker Compose?

To manage multiple containers together using a single YAML file.

---

### Q2. Difference between Docker and Docker Compose?

Docker runs one container.

Docker Compose manages multiple containers.

---

### Q3. Why use volumes?

To persist database data even if containers are deleted.

---

### Q4. Why use networks?

To allow containers to communicate securely using service names instead of IP addresses.

---

### Q5. Why use depends_on?

To control startup order.

---

### Q6. Why use health checks?

To ensure a service is actually ready before dependent services start.

---

# Real Interview Answer

**Interviewer:** Explain how your Docker Compose worked.

**Answer:**

> "Our application consisted of three services: React frontend, Node.js backend, and PostgreSQL database. Docker Compose allowed us to define all services in a single YAML file. It automatically created a private network, so the backend connected to the database using the service name instead of an IP address. We used volumes to persist PostgreSQL data and health checks to ensure the database was ready before the backend attempted to connect. During development, a single `docker compose up -d` command brought up the entire application stack."

